  • Ken T.
    Santa Clara, CA
    16
    22
    3
    3/1/2020

    This review is primarily for the Bombay and Bollywood pizzas. I've ordered from here two times, the first time I ordered a large Bombay pizza and the second time I ordered both the Bombay and Bollywood pizza. We used a coupon for a free large one-topping pizza and ate it the day after and unfortunately found the tomato sauce and cheese to be a bit bland. I'd recommend switching to buffalo milk cheese for better flavor, cook it a bit higher heat to get some brown on top of the pizza, and put a bit more italian seasoning in the sauce.

    On to the Indian pizzas! Let me start off by telling you my preferences in taste. I love Indian food and generally order Paneer / Chicken Tikka Masalas, Butter Chicken, Saag Paneer, or Vegetable Korma, and tend to stick to medium heat. So my wife and I decided to try Bay Area Pizza since it was close to our home and the reviews sounded great.

    The customer service was fantastic, the workers there have a great attitude. Feels like a lot of people do take out there, both times I went in to pick up the pizza, the shop was pretty much empty aside from a few workers. Parking lot had plenty of parking, no hassle there which is a plus.

    Bombay Pizza w/ original crust - Great tasting pizza, very generous w/ the toppings and cheese, solid flavor, not too overpowering one way or another, had a slight kick, but I'd rate it one notch below medium heat. My wife was initially a bit hesitant to try Indian pizza, but once it arrived, the smell was too good to resist and upon first bite, she fell in love w/ the pizza. The second time we ordered it, the quality was consistent and it was gone by the second day. If I had to make a suggestion, I would say add a bit more sauce and if the overall color was more orange than yellow, it would be a lot more visually appealing.

    Bollywood Pizza w/ original crust - I ordered thin crust, but it looks like it had the same thickness as the original crust, so I'll assume I received original. Compared to the Bombay pizza, the heat was quite a bit higher, I'd rate a notch above medium. The taste was amazing, definitely would recommend it. The chicken tasted like tandoori chicken to me, it was definitely flavorful. Highly recommend! If I had to change anything, I would also recommend more sauce. Perhaps doing a drizzle of butter chicken sauce after the pizza is out of the oven would make it stand out above the crowd.

    In conclusion, I would say give the Bombay or Bollywood pizzas a try, the flavor won't disappoint.
